        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-03 22:16:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nDan, do you know why your release build is failing? Seems to be nexus bad request issue. Looks like it's been failing since July 29.\n\n[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-deploy-plugin:2.7:deploy (default-deploy) on project generic-resource-api-client: Failed to deploy artifacts: Could not transfer artifact org.onap.sdnc.northbound:generic-resource-api-client:jar:1.4.0-STAGING from/to ecomp-releases (http://nexus.onap.org/content/repositories/releases): Failed to transfer file: https://nexus.onap.org/content/repositories/releases/org/onap/sdnc/northbound/generic-resource-api-client/1.4.0-STAGING/generic-resource-api-client-1.4.0-STAGING.jar. Return code is: 400, ReasonPhrase: Bad Request. -> [Help 1]",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "2d707e15b7a317b3dbadea2f1f0893bb7a9f6e66",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-08-06 13:32:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'd say maybe it's because we're adding -STAGING to version in release builds, due to issues with the staging plugin (for zip files, the staging plugin always uses the very first instance of a version saved - not the most recent - so I added -STAGING to release version to prevent daily builds from creating a version of zip that will get in the way later).  However, I made that change quite a while ago and it was working fine ... unless something changed on the LF server and now they're rejecting that tag",
        "patchset_number": 1
      }
    ]
